      }}>{`curry`}</a>{` the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`onMount`}</inlineCode>{` function? Something like `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`const onMount = onMountProps => map => { ... }`}</inlineCode>{` and then pass it into the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Map`}</inlineCode>{` as `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Map onMount={addMarkers(links)} />`}</inlineCode>{`. That was indeed my first implementation. The problem with this approach is the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Map`}</inlineCode>{` component has no way of knowing that it needs to rerender in case the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`onMountProps`}</inlineCode>{` change (say because the user clicked a button to display another marker on the map). That will only work if `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Map />`}</inlineCode>{` receives the new array of markers directly as props.`}</p>
